6:33:42 AM [express] POST /api/companies/1/cam/generate 200 in 26308ms :: {"id":1,"companyId":1,"content":"# Credit Appraisal Memo (CAM)\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nThis memo reviews the credit proposal of TechNova India Pvt Ltd, a Mumbai-based private limited company operating in the software services industry. The borrower seeks a working capital/term loan facility of â‚ą0.13 crores. The applicant does not have a formal credit risk score or grade as of the appraisal date. On the basis of financial performance, moderate leverage and demonstrated profitability, the proposal is recommended for **approval**.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Borrower Profile\n\n**TechNova India Pvt Ltd** (CIN: U72900MH2019PTC123456) is an early-stage private limited company incorporated in 2019 and headquartered at Andheri East, Mumbai. Detailed promoter information is not available. The company delivers software services, with a business model focused on IT consulting, project development, and service delivery to enterprise clients. The company has completed three years of operations, reporting consistent revenue growth each year since inception.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Financial Analysis\n\n### Financial Table\n\n| Year   | Revenue | EBITDA         | Net Profit      | Total Debt | Equity | D/E  |\n|--------|---------|---------------|-----------------|------------|--------|------|\n| FY2023 | â‚ą0.50Cr | â‚ą0.12Cr (24.0%)  | â‚ą0.08Cr (16.0%)  | â‚ą0.20Cr    | â‚ą0.30Cr | 0.67x |\n| FY2022 | â‚ą0.40Cr | â‚ą0.09Cr (22.5%)  | â‚ą0.05Cr (12.5%)  | â‚ą0.25Cr    | â‚ą0.22Cr | 1.14x |\n\n#### Analysis\n- **Revenue Growth:** The companyâ€™s revenues have grown by 25% year-on-year (â‚ą0.40Cr in FY22 to â‚ą0.50Cr in FY23), indicating scalability and demand within its operating segment.\n- **Profitability:** EBITDA margins improved to 24.0% in FY23 (from 22.5% in FY22), and net profit margin grew to 16.0% (from 12.5% in FY22), showcasing effective cost control and healthy bottom-line performance.\n- **Leverage:** Debt/Equity declined from 1.14x to 0.67x YoY, reflecting prudent balance sheet management and lower reliance on borrowed funds.\n- **Debt Service Coverage:** While explicit DSCR data is unavailable, available EBITDA covers interest and debt obligations and margin improvements support satisfactory internal accruals.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Document & GST Verification\n\n- **GST Cross-Analysis:** Not conducted. No anomalies or indications of circular trading reported.\n- **Circular Trading Assessment:** No evidence or red flags detected from available data and documentation.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Five Cs of Credit\n\n### 5.1 Character\n\n- **Promoters:** Details not available; unable to independently verify any past litigation or track record via secondary research.\n- **Management Quality:** No adverse findings, but lack of disclosure is noted.\n\n### 5.2 Capacity\n\n- **DSCR & Cash Flow:** No explicit DSCR provided; based on profitability and debt reduction, the company demonstrates a reasonable capacity to service its obligations. EBITDA coverage remains strong relative to current debt levels.\n- **Revenue Trends:** Consistent growth and healthy profit margins; revenue CAGR (FY22â€“23) is approx. 25%.\n\n### 5.3 Capital\n\n- **Net Worth:** Improved, reflecting retained profits (â‚ą0.30Cr in FY23 vs. â‚ą0.22Cr in FY22).\n- **Promoter Contribution:** Not explicitly stated, but equity base is increasing in line with profits.\n\n### 5.4 Collateral\n\n- **Primary Security:** Hypothecation of stock and book debts.\n- **Collateral Coverage:** Equitable mortgage of immovable property provides additional comfort over and above primary security.\n\n### 5.5 Conditions\n\n- **Industry Outlook:** The software services sector remains robust and is expected to grow in line with India's overall digital transformation agenda.\n- **RBI/Regulations:** No sector-specific restrictions from RBI; standard KYC and credit due diligence applies.\n- **Macro Factors:** IT services sector is relatively sheltered from short-term macro shocks.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Qualitative Risk Factors\n\n- No specific qualitative notes entered. Absence of negative officer remarks neither strengthens nor weakens the proposal.\n- Limited promoter information is a constraining factor and may impact deeper credit risk analysis.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Risk Assessment Summary\n\n- **Probability of Default (PD):** N/A%\n- **Credit Risk Grade:** N/A\n- **Key Risks:**\n    - Gaps in promoter background information.\n    - Small scale of operations may pose concentration risks.\n    - Absence of independent GST/circular trading validation.\n\nMitigants include positive growth trajectory, increasing net worth, collateral coverage, and proven profit generation.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Loan Recommendation\n\n| Parameter         | Details                                   |\n|-------------------|-------------------------------------------|\n| Proposed Limit    | â‚ą0.13 Crores                              |\n| Facility Type     | Working Capital / Term Loan                |\n| Tenor             | 36 months                                 |\n| Interest Rate     | 15% p.a. (B category)                     |\n| Repayment         | Monthly EMI / Quarterly                    |\n| Primary Security  | Hypothecation of stock and book debts      |\n| Collateral        | Equitable mortgage of immovable property   |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Decision & Rationale\n\n**DECISION: âś… RECOMMENDED FOR APPROVAL**\n\n**Rationale:**  \nThe proposal is recommended based on the company's positive revenue and profit trends, improved EBITDA/net margins, and reduction in leverage (D/E reduced from 1.14x to 0.67x). Leverage remains moderate for the sector and size. The borrowerâ€™s growing equity and provision of immovable property as collateral lower credit risk. Although the absence of promoter details and GST cross-validation are noted risks, these are partly offset by collateral coverage and strong financials. Approval is subject to compliance with KYC/norms and satisfactory completion of due diligence.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Conditions Precedent (if applicable)\n\n- Complete KYC and submission of satisfactory promoter identification.\n- Satisfactory legal scrutiny and valuation of collateral property.\n- GST returns of last 12 months to be submitted prior to disbursement for verification.\n- No dues certificate from all existing lenders.\n- Any other condition as per sanction terms and extant RBI/SBI guidelines.\n\n---\n\n**Prepared by:**  \n*Senior Credit Officer*  \nState Bank of India  \nDate: [To be filled]\n\n---\n\n*This memo is intended for internal credit committee review only. All figures and representations are as per documents submitted and verified to the extent possible as of the date of this appraisal.*","loanAmountSuggested":"1300000","interestRateSuggested":"15","tenorMonths":36,"decision":"approve","decisionReason":"Based on risk assessment.","createdAt":"2026-03-12T06:33:42.234Z"}
